"title": "5194: touch",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5194: touch",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God prohibits physical contact in certain circumstances and warns of serious consequences of violating the ritual law in this respect. Great sigificance is attached to the touch of God, Jesus Christ and angels and the disciples' touching of the risen Christ.</p>\n<h2>God's prohibits touch in certain circumstances</h2>\n<h3>At Mount Sinai</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:12-Exod19:13\">EXO 19:12–19:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:18-Heb12:24\">HEB 12:18–12:24</a></p>\n<h3>With the furnishings and articles of the tabernacle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:15\">NUM 4:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:6-2Sam6:7\">2SA 6:6–6:7</a></p>\n<h2>The law concerning touching certain articles</h2>\n<h3>Anyone or anything touching what is ritually unclean also becomes unclean</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:21-Num19:22\">NUM 19:21–19:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:2-Lev5:3\">LEV 5:2–5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:19-Lev7:21\">LEV 7:19–7:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:8\">LEV 11:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:24-Lev11:40\">LEV 11:24–11:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:4\">LEV 12:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:5-Lev15:12\">LEV 15:5–15:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:19-Lev15:27\">LEV 15:19–15:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:4-Lev22:6\">LEV 22:4–22:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:11-Num19:16\">NUM 19:11–19:16</a> <em>the law concerning dead bodies</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:8\">DEU 14:8</a> <em>Pigs are unclean</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:11\">ISA 52:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:10-Hag2:14\">HAG 2:10–2:14</a></p>\n<h3>Touching what is purified confers consecration</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:37\">EXO 29:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:29\">EXO 30:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:18\">LEV 6:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:27\">LEV 6:27</a></p>\n<h2>Man-made rules against touching certain things are condemned by Paul</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:20-Col2:22\">COL 2:20–2:22</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The touch of God</h2>\n<h3>Upon Jacob, to humble him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:25\">GEN 32:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:32\">GEN 32:32</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Upon those he calls to be prophets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:9\">JER 1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:7\">ISA 6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek2:8-Ezek3:4\">EZK 2:8–3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:16\">DAN 10:16</a></p>\n<h3>Upon the world he has made, to display his glory</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:32\">PSA 104:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:5\">PSA 144:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:5\">AMO 9:5</a></p>\n<h2>The touch of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>To heal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:3\">MAT 8:3</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:41-Mark1:42\">MRK 1:41–1:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:13\">LUK 5:13</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:29-Matt9:30\">MAT 9:29–9:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:34\">MAT 20:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:33\">MRK 7:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:22-Mark8:25\">MRK 8:22–8:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:51\">LUK 22:51</a></p>\n<h3>To raise the dead</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:18-Matt9:25\">MAT 9:18–9:25</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:22-Mark5:42\">MRK 5:22–5:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:41-Luke8:55\">LUK 8:41–8:55</a> <em>In touching the dead, Jesus Christ shows his willingness to become unclean so that others can be healed.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:14\">LUK 7:14</a></p>\n<h3>To bring reassurance and show acceptance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:6-Matt17:7\">MAT 17:6–17:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:13\">MRK 10:13</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:13\">MAT 19:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:15\">LUK 18:15</a></p>\n<h2>The touch of angels</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:5\">1KI 19:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:7\">1KI 19:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan8:18\">DAN 8:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:10\">DAN 10:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:18\">DAN 10:18</a></p>\n<h2>The reality of Jesus Christ's incarnation and resurrection is confirmed by touch</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:1\">1JN 1:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:24-John20:27\">JHN 20:24–20:27</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The figurative use of touch</h2>\n<h3>To mean harming people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek9:6\">EZK 9:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:6\">GEN 20:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:19\">JOS 9:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:22\">1CH 16:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:15\">PSA 105:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:29\">PRO 6:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech2:8-Zech2:9\">ZEC 2:8–2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:28\">HEB 11:28</a></p>\n<h3>To mean separation from sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:17\">2CO 6:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:11\">ISA 52:11</a></p>",
